


-------Setup:
    
Import:
    PyQt5.QtWidgets

Naming Scheme:
    QtWidgets.Q[WidgetName]
        
Setting up:
    
    1. app = QtWidgets.QApplication(sys.argv)
    
    2. window = QtWidgets.QMainWindow()
    
    3. widgets = QtWidgets.Q[Widget](window)
    
    4. window.show()
    
    5. app.exec_() <- underscore (exec is reserved for python)
    

------Configuring:

Size:
    
    controlled by QtCore.QRect(*args)
       
    params:
        left:
            distance from left edge
        top: 
            distance from top edge
        width:
            width
        height:
            height
            
        OR
        
        QtCore.QPoint:
            top left point (?)
        QtCore.QPoint:
            bottom right point (?)
        
        OR
        
        QtCore.QPoint:
            top left point (?)
        QtCore.QSize:
            width/height (?)   
           
    rect = QtCore.QRect(*args)
    widget.setGeometry(rect)
    
    locations are relative to the parent widget!
    for top-level widgets, locations are relative to screen!
    
    
    
---------Signals and Slots:

Without Args:
    widget.signalname.connect(receiving function)
   
With Args:
    widget.signalname['ArgType'].connect(receiving function)
    
Arg Types:
    
    QString -> string wrapper class (?)
    QModelIndex -> int wrapper class (?)
    bool -> Python int or true/false (?)
    QPoint -> tuple (x,y) wrapper class (?)
    QObject* -> QObject wrapper class (?)
    
    